  "body": "E.g, when I generate list of buttons, I want to assign every button to same array, which is accessible through `this.refs`. After that, I can perform operation on every button easily. Something like square bracket syntax `<input type=\"text\" name=\"input[]\" />` in html.\n\n``` javascript\nvar ButtonList = React.createClass({\n    render: function() {\n        return (\n            {this.props.buttons.map(function(button) {\n                return <MyButton ref=\"buttons[]\" onClick={this.handleClick} label={button.label} />;\n            })}\n        );\n    },\n    handleClick: function() {\n        this.refs.buttons.forEach(function(button) {\n            // perform operation on button\n        });\n    }\n});\n```\n",
